Recommended UI/UX Tooling : 
Penpot export tool - Locofy.ai: Can help convert Penpot designs directly into React code, including token integration.   
Penpot design tool – for Style Dictionary or Amazon Theo to transform those JSON files into platform-specific outputs:  
Figma design tool - Tokens Studio for FigmaAllows designers to push/pull tokens from GitHub to Figma.Style DictionaryConverts your JSON tokens into CSS, JS, and iOS/Android formats. 
Example - Would you like to see a sample style-dictionary.config.js that demonstrates how to generate both CSS for React and USS for Unity from a single Penpot JSON?  
Shared "Design Tokens" (in packages/ui) For a perfect cycle between a Vite web app and a potential mobile/desktop shell: The Need: Hardcoded Tailwind classes or CSS will break on non-web platforms. The Fix: Export a theme.ts (JSON-like) from ui containing colors, spacing, and typography. Use these tokens to generate your CSS for Web and your Objects for Native/Unity. 
Incorporating a Design Token Dictionary is the final step to "closing the loop" 

 
The "Perfect Cycle" Workflow 
Design Side: Designers manage variables in Figma. 
The Bridge: Use a plugin like Tokens Studio or Figma's native Variables API to sync these values directly to your packages/tokens folder via a GitHub PR. 
Automated Build: When the JSON changes, Turbo triggers a build of packages/tokens. 
Propagation: packages/ui and all your apps/ immediately inherit the new branding or spacing changes upon the next deploy. 
  
 
 
tokens.css / tokens.scss for the Web apps. 
tokens.ts for your React components.  
tokens.json for Unity/Native apps. 
 
 
